The positive reception to President Joe Biden’s 2024 State of the Union address hasn’t pulled him ahead of former President Donald Trump in our early tracking of the race, but there are signs that it is assuaging some voter concerns about his age — particularly among his own base.&nbsp;
According to Morning Consult’s weekly tracking surveys conducted before and after his March 7 speech, the share of voters who said Biden is “too old” fell slightly compared with the previous week, from 68% to 65%, while the share who disagreed with the sentiment grew from 26% to 30%.

